tes was shaped by eugenicists. This book will be of interest not only to disability and eugenic scholars and historians, but to anyone who wants to explore the means by which pejorative metaphors are used to support social control efforts against vulnerable community groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEugenicszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aInvoluntary sterilizationzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / People with Disabilities.2bisacsh  aAmerican Eugenic Movement.  aEugenics.  aFeeble-Mindedness.  aMetaphor Analysis.1 aO’Brien, Gerald V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610342040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526103420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526103420/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles